'''Domestic violence in Uganda''' is a problem as it is in many parts of Africa.<ref>{{cite news | title=Sensitise Ugandans and enforce the existing laws against domestic violence | work=[[Daily Monitor]] | url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/OpEd/Letters/Sensitise-Ugandans-enforce-the-existing-laws-domestic-violence/-/806314/1754528/-/10kvljyz/-/index.html | accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dfid.gov.uk/casestudies/files/africa/uganda-domestic-violence.asp | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928184116/http://www.dfid.gov.uk/casestudies/files/africa/uganda-domestic-violence.asp | title=DFID - Case Studies - Saying “No” to domestic violence in Uganda | archivedate=28 September 2008 | accessdate=19 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.opendemocracy.net/content/african-women-and-domestic-violence | title=African women and domestic violence | work=openDemocracy | accessdate=19 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://blogs.worldbank.org/africacan/domestic-violence-and-poverty-in-africa-when-the-husbands-beatin | title=Domestic Violence and Poverty in Africa: When the Husband’s Beating Stick is Like Butter | work=AfricaCan End Poverty | accessdate=19 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.justice.gov/sites/default/files/eoir/legacy/2013/11/07/UGA102881.E.pdf | title=RESPONSES TO INFORMATION REQUESTS (RIRs) | website=Justice.gov | format=PDF | accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.who.int/bulletin/Koenig0103.pdf | format=PDF | title=Domestic violence in rural Uganda: evidence from a community-based study | website=Who.int | accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.loc.gov/law/foreign-news/article/uganda-women-judges-voice-concern-over-domestic-violence/ |title=Uganda: Women Judges Voice Concern over Domestic Violence &#124; Global Legal Monitor | website=Loc.gov | accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>

There is a deep cultural belief in Uganda that it is socially acceptable to hit a woman to discipline her.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development-professionals-network/2014/aug/29/domestic-violence-uganda|title='Beating your wife is a sign of love' - changing norms to end domestic abuse|first=Tanya|last=Abramsky|date=29 August 2014|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Are Women provocative|work= [[The Independent (Uganda)|Independent]]|date= |url= http://www.independent.co.ug/features/features/2763-are-ugandan-men-violent-or-are-the-women-provocative|accessdate= 2014-03-24|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140325020000/http://www.independent.co.ug/features/features/2763-are-ugandan-men-violent-or-are-the-women-provocative|archivedate= 2014-03-25|df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Ugandan domestic violence bill stalls|work= [[The Guardian]]|date=|url= https://www.theguardian.com/katine/2010/mar/18/uganda-domestic-violence-bill|accessdate=2014-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Domestic violence cases soar|work= [[New Vision]]|date=|url= http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/644085-domestic-violence-cases-soar.html|accessdate=2014-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Uganda tackles wife-beating taboo|work= [[BBC]]|date=|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/1881472.stm|accessdate=2014-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://paa2013.princeton.edu/papers/130441 |format=PDF |title=Title: Educational Attainment and Domestic Violence in Uganda |website=Paa2013.princeton.edu |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref>

Wife beating costs the Ugandan economy billions of shillings per year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1339130/uganda-loses-sh77bn-domestic-violence |title=Uganda Loses Sh77bn To Domestic Violence Cases |website=Newvision.co.ug |date=2014-03-28 |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1326037/domestic-violence-affecting-quality-uganda-population |title=Domestic Violence Affecting Quality Of Uganda’s Population |website=Newvision.co.ug |date=2013-07-11 |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://fsu.digital.flvc.org/islandora/object/fsu:181762/datastream/PDF/view |format=PDF |title=Florida State University Libraries |website=Fsu.digital.flvx.org |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acordinternational.org/silo/files/uganda-an-audit-of-legal-practice-on-sexual-violence.pdf |format=PDF |title=Making the law count |website=Acordinternational.org |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref>

