The '''Akanigui''' (also '''Kanigui''' or '''Bakaniki''') are an ethnic group in [[Gabon]]. They live in the [[Haut-Ogooué]] region, northwest of [[Franceville]].<ref name="Olson1996">{{cite book|author=James Stuart Olson|title=The Peoples of Africa: An Ethnohistorical Dictionary|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MdaAdBC-_S4C&pg=PA271|accessdate=30 March 2012|year=1996|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-27918-8|page=271}}</ref>
They speak a [[Bantu language]], the [[Kaningi language]], whose number of speakers was estimated at 19,901 in 6000. There was about 6,000 Akanigui in Gabon in 1990.

