* [[Risk management]] &ndash; management specialism aiming to reduce different risks related to a preselected domain to the level accepted by society. It may include numerous types of threats caused by environment, technology, humans, organizations, and politics.
* [[Skills management]] &ndash; 
* [[Spend management]] &ndash; 
* [[Strategic management]] &ndash; 
* [[Strategic planning]] &ndash; 
* [[Systems management]] &ndash; 
* [[Management science]] &ndash; (MS), is the discipline of using mathematical modeling and other analytical methods, to help make better business management decisions.
* [[Nonlinear management]] &ndash; (NLM) superset of management techniques and strategies that allows order to emerge by giving organizations the space to self-organize, evolve and adapt, encompassing Agile, Evolutionary and Lean approaches, as well as many others.
* [[Operations management]] &ndash; area of business that is concerned with the production of good quality goods and services, and involves the responsibility of ensuring that business operations are efficient and effective. It is the management of resources, the distribution of goods and services to customers, and the analysis of queue systems.
* [[Scientific management]] &ndash; theory of management that analyzes and synthesizes workflow processes, improving labor productivity.

